'''Frigger''' is an [[Australian]] [[colloquial]] term given to individuals whom speak with [[broad Australian English]] accents that partake in activities such as [[Bachelor and Spinster Balls]] and [[Ute Muster|Ute Musters]]. Generally a derogatory term (but not always) used to [[satirises]] the rural Australian [[stereotypes]]. Exclusively used in rural Australia.

Generally the alcohol [[Bundaberg Rum]] is associated with ''Friggers''. Known colloquially as 'Bundy'.

The Australian suburban equivalent term is [[Bogan]].

